# WiFi SERVER - ESP32

## Description
Use ESP32 as a Local Server Host, to Host a Webpage 

## Hardware
- ESP32 Dev Board
- USB Cable

## Features
- Host a Simple Website
- Turn and off and LED 

## How to Use
1. Flash firmware to ESP32
2. Open Serial Monitor at 115200 baud
3. Networks will scan every 5 seconds

## Pin Configuration
| Pin | Function |
|-----|----------|
| GPIO 2 | Onboard LED |

## Notes
## WIFI MODE
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_AP);   //  Access Point (Server/Host)
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_STA);  // Station (Client)
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_AP_STA); //  Both AP and Client at same time
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_OFF);  // Turn WiFi off

## Valid Subnet Masks Only
Subnet Mask | Binary Last Octet | Hosts Allowed
255.255.255.0 00000000 254
255.255.255.128 10000000 126 
255.255.255.192 11000000 62
255.255.255.224 11100000 30
255.255.255.240 11110000 14
255.255.255.248 11111000 6
255.255.255.252 11111100 2

## Other Common Subnet Masks
Subnet | Max Devices | Use Case
255.255.255.0 254 Home/small network
255.255.0.0 65,534 Large network
255.0.0.0 16 million Very large network

## Parameter	Your Value	Meaning
ssid	"KTEK_HOST"	Network name
password	"12345678"	Network password
channel	1	WiFi channel (1-13)
hidden	0	0 = visible, 1 = hidden network
max_connection	1-10	Max devices allowed


## Limits
Default	4 devices
Minimum	1 device
Maximum	10 devices